occurrenceRemarks: This organism is known as a Saw Palmetto. It is a fern that has leaves that are about 2 feet long each, growing from a base that is about one foot from the ground. The ferns are a vibrant green, though the ferns that I observed were seen to have black spots on the leaves. This organism was found in a forest habitat in cool, dry, and breezy 60 degree Fahrenheit weather. They appear in large colonies as many were seen along the nature trail paths in Lettuce Lake Park. The shrubs are usually 10-12 feet and occasioanlly become small trees after some time. Their fruit are orange to black when matured (Wildflower). Plant Database. (2014, September 5). Retrieved February 23, 2020, from https://www.wildflower.org/plants/result.php?id_plant=sere2
